The Bacillus thuringiensis Market is expected to grow from USD 240.90 Million in 2022 to USD 371.90 Million by 2030, at a CAGR of 6.40% during the forecast period.

The Bacillus thuringiensis market is expected to grow at a CAGR of 6.40% from 2022 to 2030, fueled by the increasing demand for natural and eco-friendly pest control solutions. Bacillus thuringiensis is a naturally occurring bacterium that produces proteins toxic to a variety of insects, making it an effective and sustainable alternative to chemical pesticides. APAC is expected to be the fastest-growing region due to its large agricultural sector and the rising demand for organic food. The global Bacillus thuringiensis market is expected to reach USD 371.90 Million by 2030, with increased adoption of sustainable agriculture practices driving growth.

