MARKET BY REGION
Bacillus thuringiensis is a popular biopesticide that has seen a steady growth in demand in the recent years. North America and Europe are the leading markets due to the strict regulations and preference for organic produce. However, the APAC region is expected to witness the highest growth due to the increasing demand for biopesticides and the promotion of sustainable agriculture by governments. The USA is another market that has seen a considerable growth in demand due to the focus on reducing chemical pesticide use. China, being the largest farming country, is anticipated to have a significant market share, with an increasing demand for biopesticides and sustainable agriculture in the country.

The Bacillus thuringiensis market is expected to be dominated by North America, followed by Europe and Asia Pacific. North America is expected to have the largest market share percent valuation due to the increasing demand for organic and natural insecticides in the region. In addition, the presence of major key players in the region is expected to contribute to the growth of the market.

Europe is also expected to have a significant share in the Bacillus thuringiensis market, owing to the rising demand for environment-friendly and sustainable agriculture practices. Furthermore, strict regulations regarding the use of synthetic chemicals in agriculture are also expected to boost the market growth in the region.

The Asia Pacific is also anticipated to witness significant growth in the Bacillus thuringiensis market due to the increasing population and growing demand for food products. In addition, the rising awareness about the harmful effects of synthetic chemicals on the environment and human health is also expected to contribute to the growth of the market in the region.

The expected market share of the Bacillus thuringiensis market in North America is estimated to be around 40%, while Europe and Asia Pacific are expected to account for 30% and 25%, respectively. The remaining 5% market share is expected to be held by the rest of the world.

