MARKET BY COMPANY
Bacillus thuringiensis (Bt) market has experienced rapid growth in recent years owing to the rising demand for eco-friendly pest control solutions. Several players dominate the Bt market globally, including Sumitomo Chemical, Certis USA, FMC, Fujian Pucheng Green Shell Biopesticide, King Biotec, Shaanxi Microbe Biotechnology, Wuhan Unioasis Biological, Wuhan Kernel Bio-tech, Yangzhou Luyuan Bio-Chemical, Phyllom BioProducts Corporation, Bonide, and Becker Microbial Products.

Sumitomo Chemical and Certis USA are the leaders in the Bt market, accounting for a significant market share. These companies offer a wide range of products based on Bt, including insecticides, fungicides, and bactericides. FMC Corporation, on the other hand, focuses on developing and commercializing innovative biotechnology products. Fujian Pucheng Green Shell Biopesticide, Yangzhou Luyuan Bio-Chemical, and Shaanxi Microbe Biotechnology are some of the key Chinese companies operating in the Bt market.

King Biotec, Wuhan Unioasis Biological, Wuhan Kernel Bio-tech, Phyllom BioProducts Corporation, Bonide, and Becker Microbial Products also offer a range of Bt-based products. These companies have been expanding their product portfolio and strengthening their distribution channels to cater to the rising demand for Bt-based products globally.

Sumitomo Chemical reported net sales of $19.5 billion in FY2020. Certis USA, a subsidiary of Mitsui & Co., reported sales of $1.1 billion in 2019. FMC Corporation generated sales of $4.6 billion in 2020, and Phyllom BioProducts Corporation reported revenue of $4.3 million in 2020.

In conclusion, the Bt market is dominated by a few key players who offer a wide range of Bt-based products. These companies are constantly expanding their product portfolio and strengthening their distribution channels to cater to the rising demand for eco-friendly pest control solutions. The market is expected to continue growing over the coming years owing to the increasing awareness of the harmful effects of chemical pesticides and the growing demand for sustainable agriculture practices.

