MARKET BY APPLICATIONS
Bacillus thuringiensis (Bt) is a biopesticide widely used in agriculture for controlling pests that damage fruit and vegetables, crops, and forests. It is an effective alternative to synthetic pesticides as it is environmentally friendly and does not harm beneficial organisms such as birds, bees, and other insects. Bt is also used in urban greening and gardening to control pests on plants and lawns. In addition, Bt is used in vector control programs to control mosquitoes that carry diseases such as malaria and dengue fever. Bt produces crystal proteins that are toxic to target insects, disrupting their digestive system and killing them.

The fastest-growing application segment of Bt in terms of revenue is the crop protection sector. The demand for Bt biopesticides is increasing as farmers are adopting sustainable farming practices and reducing the use of synthetic chemicals. In addition, the global biopesticide market is growing due to the increasing awareness of the harmful effects of chemical pesticides on human health and the environment. The use of Bt in fruit and vegetable production is also growing, driven by consumer demand for pesticide-free produce. Overall, the application of Bt is expanding as more industries recognize its potential as a safe and effective pest control solution.

